HEADWORD: Fireweed
<hw>Fire"weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An American plant (<spn>Erechthites
hiercifolia</spn>), very troublesome in spots where brushwood has been
burned.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The great willow-herb (<spn>Epilobium
spicatum</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

